The earth's posture is receptive;
A nobleman should bear the burden of things with generous virtue.

Stepping on frost indicates hard ice;
Yin is beginning to coagulate. Following this path leads to solid ice.

The movement of the second six is straightforward and four-directional;
Not practicing brings no disadvantage, for the earth's way is radiant.

Containing brilliance may be correct;
It times to manifest. Perhaps following royal affairs shows great brightness.

Tying up a sack brings no harm;
Careful, one comes to no harm.

The yellow garment is greatly auspicious;
The ornament is within.

The dragon fights in the wilds;
The way is at its end.

Clouds and thunder form Difficulty at the Beginning;
A nobleman should arrange affairs as in weaving silk.

Though he lingers at the threshold, his will and conduct are correct.
By honoring the humble, he greatly wins the people.

The difficulty of the second six comes from riding upon the yang;
After ten years he marries, returning to the proper way.

Chasing the deer without a forester means pursuing the quarry;
A nobleman abandons it; going brings regret and poverty.

Seeking and going indicates clarity.

Accumulating wealth in Difficulty at the Beginning leaves brightness unfulfilled.

Weeping blood flows continuously;
How can this last?
